      "writtenOn": "2020-12-22T03:32:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I know you added testsToSkip/testsNotInShard to results to avoid \"One or more test patterns did not match any tests\" error. However, this results in inconsistency between results.json and streamed_results.jsonl. For example:\n\n $ ~/trunk/src/platform/tast/fast_build.sh \u0026\u0026 ~/go/bin/tast run -totalshards\u003d2 -shardindex\u003d0 localhost:2222 meta.LocalPass meta.RemotePass\n ...\n 2020/12/22 03:25:45 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n 2020/12/22 03:25:45 meta.RemotePass  [ SKIP ] test is not in the specified shard\n 2020/12/22 03:25:45 meta.LocalPass   [ PASS ]\n 2020/12/22 03:25:45 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n $ cat /tmp/tast/results/latest/results.json\n \u003d\u003e contains results for meta.RemotePass and meta.LocalPass\n\n $ cat /tmp/tast/results/latest/streamed_results.jsonl\n \u003d\u003e contains results for meta.LocalPass only!\n\n\nI guess we can update unmatchedTestPatterns to compare results with cfg.testNames, not with cfg.Patterns, to resolve the error.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 46
      },
      "revId": "b48ead3fbd2f70f9a90886ed9752b44046cfdd66",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
